# Cross-Module Agent Isolation
Agents must NEVER read files outside their assigned module boundary. When backend and frontend agents work in parallel:
- **Backend agents** read only `constat/`, `tests/`, `docs/`. Never read `constat-ui/`.
- **Frontend agents** read only `constat-ui/`. Never read `constat/` or `tests/`.
- Shared contracts (GraphQL field names, API shapes) come from the **plan/task description**, not from reading the other module's source code.
- If an agent needs information about the other module, it must ask the team lead — not read the files directly.

# Teammate Spawn Context
Include: 1) Module(s) they own  2) Files to read first  3) Verification command  4) What NOT to touch  5) Explicit `model` parameter